# GetTidyData CodeBook

The run_analysis.R script performs the following steps to obtain the tidy dataset:

1. Combine the traning and testing datasets in to the final merged dataset by using read.table() and row combine (rbind())

2. Read the general datasets include the subject, workout activity, activity labels, and the features datasets 

3. A function (checkStats()) is applied to the features dataset to select only measurements of average (mean()) and standard deviation (std()).

4. The subject, activity, labels and selected features datasets are joined into the final dataset

5. The dataset is melt by subject and activity and dcast is applied to compte the mean of selected measurements


